legre.</p><p> Bernstein, the son of Jewish-Ukrainian immigrants to the US, was a renowned composer and conductor perhaps best known for writing the music to <em>West Side Story</em> .</p><p> Earlier this month, <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/leonard-bernsteins-family-defend-bradley-cooper-maestro-prosthetic-nose-backlash-3483986">Bernstein&#39;s family similarly defended Cooper&#39;s decision</a> to use prosthetics for the role.</p><p> “It breaks our hearts to see any misrepresentations or misunderstandings of his efforts,” Bernstein&#39;s children, Jamie, Alexander and Nina, said. “It happens to be true that Leonard Bernstein had a nice, big nose. Bradley chose to use makeup to amplify his resemblance, and we&#39;re perfectly fine with that.”</p><p> Last month, the casting of non-Jewish actor Cillian Murphy in the lead role of Christopher Nolan&#39;s <em>Oppenheimer</em> , a Jewish nuclear physicist, <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/david-baddiel-questions-cillian-murphy-casting-jewish-oppenheimer-3476449">faced scrutiny from David Baddiel</a> .</p><p> In an article on the <a href="https://www.thejc.com/lets-talk/all/oppenheimer-liked-to-pretend-he-wasn't-jewish-like-the-film-1rsH6pz4EC1yDIku5F1azk" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Jewish Chronicle</em></a> , Baddiel wrote: “Yet again, a major movie has cast a non-Jew to play a famous Jew. This may be part of a deeper erasure of Jews – and anti-semitism – going on under the surface of storytelling.”</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/bradley-coopers-prosthetic-nose-defended-against-jewface-anti-defamation-league-3486585">Bradley Cooper&#39;s prosthetic nose defended against “Jewface” criticism by Anti-Defamation League</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
 'Oppenheimer' composer says Cillian Murphy's “almost inhuman” performance changed the score https://www.nme.com/news/film/oppenheimer-cillian-murphy-performance-changed-score-ludwig-goransson-3486551?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=oppenheimer-cillian-murphy-performance-changed-score-ludwig-goranssonAdam Starkey Tue, 22 Aug 2023 11:17:29 +0000 Film NewsNews https://www.nme.com/?p=3486551 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Oppenheimer_Cillian_Murphy-1.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="奥本海默" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Oppenheimer_Cillian_Murphy-1.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Oppenheimer_Cillian_Murphy-1-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Oppenheimer_Cillian_Murphy-1-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Oppenheimer_Cillian_Murphy-1-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Oppenheimer_Cillian_Murphy-1-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Oppenheimer_Cillian_Murphy-1-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> “It feels like it becomes a part of you”</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/oppenheimer-cillian-murphy-performance-changed-score-ludwig-goransson-3486551">&#39;Oppenheimer&#39; composer says Cillian Murphy&#39;s “almost inhuman” performance changed the score</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Oppenheimer_Cillian_Murphy-1.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="奥本海默" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Oppenheimer_Cillian_Murphy-1.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Oppenheimer_Cillian_Murphy-1-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Oppenheimer_Cillian_Murphy-1-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Oppenheimer_Cillian_Murphy-1-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Oppenheimer_Cillian_Murphy-1-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Oppenheimer_Cillian_Murphy-1-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/films/oppenheimer"><em>Oppenheimer</em></a> composer <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/ludwig-goransson">Ludwig Göransson</a> has explained how <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/cillian-murphy">Cillian Murphy&#39;s</a> performance shaped the film&#39;s score.</p><p> Murphy plays the lead role of physicist J. Robert Oppenheimer in <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/christopher-nolan">Christopher Nolan&#39;s</a> historical drama, which follows the creation of the first nuclear weapons under the Manhattan Project.</p><ul><li> <strong>READ MORE: <a href="https://www.nme.com/features/film-interviews/oppenheimer-score-soundtrack-ludwig-goransson-christopher-nolan-3471661">“It was unplayable”: &#39;Oppenheimer&#39; composer Ludwig Göransson wrote Nolan&#39;s toughest score yet</a></strong></li></ul><p> Speaking to <a href="https://www.nme.com/features/film-interviews/oppenheimer-score-soundtrack-ludwig-goransson-christopher-nolan-3471661"><em>NME</em></a> , Göransson, who previously collaborated with Nolan on films <em>Dunkirk</em> and <em>Tenet</em> , said the score for <em>Oppenheimer</em> would have “absolutely” been different if another actor had portrayed the titular scientist.</p><p> “With [Murphy&#39;s] performance, you&#39;re just living it, you&#39;re breathing it, you&#39;re taking it home,” he said. “It feels like it becomes part of you. That did influence the music when I was writing it.” </p><figure id="attachment_2765968" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-2765968" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-2765968" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Ludwig_Göransson.jpg" alt="Ludwig Göransson" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Ludwig_Göransson.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Ludwig_Göransson-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Ludwig_Göransson-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Ludwig_Göransson-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Ludwig_Göransson-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Ludwig_Göransson-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-2765968" class="wp-caption-text"> Ludwig Göransson, winner of two Grammy awards for producing Childish Gambino&#39;s &#39;This Is America&#39;. Credit: Getty</figcaption></figure><p> Describing his performance as “almost inhuman”, the composer explained how they came up with a recurring theme to match Murphy&#39;s depiction of the character.</p><p> “One of the early ideas that Chris [Nolan] had was the use of the violin,” Göransson said. “Oppenheimer was a genius with a lot of complex layers underneath.</p><p> “With a solo violin, you can play the most beautiful, romantic vibrato. But then if you press down the bow heavily and change the speed, you can make something horrific, manic or neurotic in a split second… Chris and I were constantly talking about going in and out of different emotions.”</p><p> Since it was released last month, <em>Oppenheimer</em> has become the fourth highest-grossing movie of the year, behind <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/film-reviews/super-mario-bros-movie-review-chris-pratt-3425797"><em>The Super Mario Bros. Movie</em></a> ,<a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/film-reviews/barbie-review-margot-robbie-ryan-gosling-3470019"><em>Barbie</em></a> and <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/film-reviews/guardians-of-the-galaxy-volume-3-review-james-gunn-3437058"><em>Guardians Of The Galaxy Vol. 3</em></a> .</p><p> In a <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/film-reviews/oppenheimer-review-christopher-nolan-3470392">five-star review</a> , <em>NME</em> wrote: “Not just the definitive account of the man behind the atom bomb, <em>Oppenheimer</em> is a monumental achievement in grown-up filmmaking.</p><p> “For years, Nolan has been perfecting the art of the serious blockbuster – crafting smart, finely-tuned multiplex epics that demand attention; that can&#39;t be watched anywhere other than in a cinema, uninterrupted, without distractions. But this, somehow, feels bigger.”</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/oppenheimer-cillian-murphy-performance-changed-score-ludwig-goransson-3486551">&#39;Oppenheimer&#39; composer says Cillian Murphy&#39;s “almost inhuman” performance changed the score</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
